-- Long prose bios
UPDATE employees SET bio = 'Michael Gary Scott is the regional manager of the Dunder Mifflin Scranton branch, a position he has held with great enthusiasm and questionable judgment since the early 2000s. Known for his catchphrases, improv comedy background, and an unwavering belief that he is the world''s best boss, Michael leads his team through a chaotic blend of heart, humor, and the occasional inappropriate comment. When he is not planning the next office party or filming his action movie Threat Level Midnight, he can be found mentoring employees he affectionately considers his family.' WHERE id = 1;
UPDATE employees SET bio = 'Dwight Kurt Schrute III is the ambitious and fiercely loyal Assistant to the Regional Manager at Dunder Mifflin Scranton, though he would much prefer the title of Assistant Regional Manager. A beet farmer by trade and a martial artist by passion, Dwight runs Schrute Farms, a working agrotourism destination famous for its table-making workshops and eccentric bed and breakfast. His rivalry with coworker Jim Halpert is the stuff of legend, as is his encyclopedic knowledge of bears, beets, and Battlestar Galactica.' WHERE id = 2;
UPDATE employees SET bio = 'James Duncan Halpert is a sales representative whose deadpan wit and effortless charm make him the office''s resident prankster and voice of reason. Though he started as a temp with dreams of something bigger, Jim found his stride at Dunder Mifflin and, more importantly, found Pam, the receptionist who became his wife. Whether he is orchestrating an elaborate prank on Dwight or simply looking into the camera for validation, Jim keeps the Scranton branch grounded in sanity.' WHERE id = 3;
UPDATE employees SET bio = 'Pamela Morgan Beesly began her career answering phones at the Dunder Mifflin front desk, but she is far more than the office receptionist. An aspiring artist with a quiet strength and a sharp sense of humor, Pam gradually grew into a confident office administrator and designer, organizing parties, painting murals, and eventually pursuing her creative dreams in Philadelphia. Her romance with Jim is the emotional heart of the office, proof that sometimes the best stories start across a cluttered desk.' WHERE id = 4;
UPDATE employees SET bio = 'Kevin Malone is the lovable, perpetually confused accountant whose simple exterior hides a genuine talent for numbers and a surprising gift for music. A drummer in his own band, Kevin approaches both spreadsheets and chili preparation with unbridled enthusiasm and a relaxed sense of urgency. He may waste time saying a lot of words when few words do the trick, but he is a beloved fixture of the Scranton branch.' WHERE id = 7;
UPDATE employees SET bio = 'Stanley Hudson is the office''s most devoted pretzel enthusiast and a man who firmly believes that the workday begins and ends exactly when it is scheduled to, no more and no less. A senior sales representative, Stanley tolerates the chaos of the Scranton branch with stoic patience, reserving his rare bursts of energy for Pretzel Day and his escape to Florida each winter. Do not disturb him during lunch, and whatever you do, never make him repeat himself.' WHERE id = 10;
UPDATE employees SET bio = 'David Wallace is the Chief Financial Officer of Dunder Mifflin and the corporate executive to whom the Scranton branch reports. A polished, thoughtful leader who genuinely tries to do right by the company, David is repeatedly tested by Michael''s antics, corporate machinations, and the slow decline of the paper industry. When the pressure of corporate life becomes too much, he retreats to his lake house to sail and work on his doomed novelty toy, Suck It.' WHERE id = 19;
UPDATE employees SET bio = 'Holly Parallax Flax is the HR representative who transferred to Scranton and quickly became Michael''s soulmate, matching his awkward humor beat for beat. Kind, quirky, and unflappably earnest, Holly brought a warmth to the office that even Toby could not manage. Her romance with Michael is one of the few storylines in which the Scranton branch gets a genuinely happy ending.' WHERE id = 21;

